Definition.WordDefinition: Innermost \In"ner*most`\ ([i^]n"n[~e]r*m[=o]st`), a. [A corruption of inmost due to influence of inner. See {Inmost}.] Farthest inward; most remote from the outward part; inmost; deepest within. --Prov. xviii. 8. [1913 Webster]
innermost adj 1: being deepest within the self; "one's innermost feelings" [syn: {inmost}] 2: situated or occurring farthest within; "the innermost chamber" [syn: {inmost}]
